cjnIpv4.name: cjnIpv4
cjnIpv4.contactinfo: Erick Crowell -- ecrowell@lucent.com Raj Duggal (Group Leader) -- rduggal@lucent.com Ira Steckler -- isteckler@lucent.com
cjnIpv4.description: Cajun Private IP version 4 mib extentions

cjnIpEnabled.name: cjnIpEnabled
cjnIpEnabled.description: Enable / Disable IP Unicast on this system.

cjnIpMCEnabled.name: cjnIpMCEnabled
cjnIpMCEnabled.description: Enable or disable IP multicast on a global basis. This will affect all IP interfaces set up to use multicast protocols.

cjnIpRteEnabled.name: cjnIpRteEnabled
cjnIpRteEnabled.description: Enable / Disable IP Routing on this system.

cjnIpSSREnabled.name: cjnIpSSREnabled
cjnIpSSREnabled.description: Enable / Disable the use of IP Source Routing.

cjnMaxRoutes.name: cjnMaxRoutes
cjnMaxRoutes.description: Specify the maximum number of routes that can be added to the routing table. Note that these routes refer only to IP Unicast entries.

cjnMaxArpCacheEntries.name: cjnMaxArpCacheEntries
cjnMaxArpCacheEntries.description: Specify the maximum number of ARP cache entries. Refers to the space available for the IP address table. When you increase the number of entries, it may cause the table to be relearned more frequently. Consequently, it will make address space usage more efficient.

cjnIpGlobalStatsReset.name: cjnIpGlobalStatsReset
cjnIpGlobalStatsReset.description: When set to the value enable (1) all IP Global statistics are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(2)

cjnProxyArpLimit.name: cjnProxyArpLimit
cjnProxyArpLimit.description: Enable or disable Proxy ARP on the same network. When enabled, the router will only respond to ARP requests when the source and target IP address are in the same IP network and different IP subnets. When disabled, the router will only respond to ARP requests when the source and target IP address are in different networks.

cjnProxyArpDefRte.name: cjnProxyArpDefRte
cjnProxyArpDefRte.description: Enable or disable the use of the default route on your Cajun switch as the route for Proxy ARPs.

cjnLocalRtePref.name: cjnLocalRtePref
cjnLocalRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of Local Routes.

cjnRIPRtePref.name: cjnRIPRtePref
cjnRIPRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of RIP Routes.

cjnOSPFIntraAreaRtePref.name: cjnOSPFIntraAreaRtePref
cjnOSPFIntraAreaRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of OSPF Intra-area Routes.

cjnOSPFExternalRtePref.name: cjnOSPFExternalRtePref
cjnOSPFExternalRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of OSPF External Routes.

cjnHighPrefStaticRtePref.name: cjnHighPrefStaticRtePref
cjnHighPrefStaticRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of High-preference Static Routes.

cjnLowPrefStaticRtePref.name: cjnLowPrefStaticRtePref
cjnLowPrefStaticRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of Low-preference Static Routes.

cjnOSPFInterAreaRtePref.name: cjnOSPFInterAreaRtePref
cjnOSPFInterAreaRtePref.description: The Routing Preference of OSPF Inter-area Routes.

cjnIpInReceives.name: cjnIpInReceives
cjnIpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

cjnIpInHdrErrors.name: cjnIpInHdrErrors
cjnIpInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

cjnIpInAddrErrors.name: cjnIpInAddrErrors
cjnIpInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP Gateways and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was nota local address.

cjnIpForwDatagrams.name: cjnIpForwDatagrams
cjnIpForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP Gateways, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source- Route option processing was successful.

cjnIpInUnknownProtos.name: cjnIpInUnknownProtos
cjnIpInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

cjnIpInDiscards.name: cjnIpInDiscards
cjnIpInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

cjnIpInDelivers.name: cjnIpInDelivers
cjnIpInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

cjnIpOutRequests.name: cjnIpOutRequests
cjnIpOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

cjnIpOutDiscards.name: cjnIpOutDiscards
cjnIpOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

cjnIpOutNoRoutes.name: cjnIpOutNoRoutes
cjnIpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagarms which a host cannot route because all of its default gateways are down.

cjnIpReasmTimeout.name: cjnIpReasmTimeout
cjnIpReasmTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

cjnIpReasmReqds.name: cjnIpReasmReqds
cjnIpReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

cjnIpReasmOKs.name: cjnIpReasmOKs
cjnIpReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully re- assembled.

cjnIpReasmFails.name: cjnIpReasmFails
cjnIpReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re- assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

cjnIpFragOKs.name: cjnIpFragOKs
cjnIpFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

cjnIpFragFails.name: cjnIpFragFails
cjnIpFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

cjnIpFragCreates.name: cjnIpFragCreates
cjnIpFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

cjnIpRoutingDiscards.name: cjnIpRoutingDiscards
cjnIpRoutingDiscards.description: The number of routing entries which were chosen to be discarded even though they are valid. One possible reason for discarding such an entry could be to free-up buffer space for other routing entries.

cjnIcmpInMsgs.name: cjnIcmpInMsgs
cjnIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpInErrors.

cjnIcmpInErrors.name: cjnIcmpInErrors
cjnIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

cjnIcmpInDestUnreachs.name: cjnIcmpInDestUnreachs
cjnIcmpInDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

cjnIcmpInTimeExcds.name: cjnIcmpInTimeExcds
cjnIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

cjnIcmpInParmProbs.name: cjnIcmpInParmProbs
cjnIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

cjnIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: cjnIcmpInSrcQuenchs
cjnIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

cjnIcmpInRedirects.name: cjnIcmpInRedirects
cjnIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages received.

cjnIcmpInEchos.name: cjnIcmpInEchos
cjnIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received.

cjnIcmpInEchoReps.name: cjnIcmpInEchoReps
cjnIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages received.

cjnIcmpInTimestamps.name: cjnIcmpInTimestamps
cjnIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages received.

cjnIcmpInTimestampReps.name: cjnIcmpInTimestampReps
cjnIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

cjnIcmpInAddrMasks.name: cjnIcmpInAddrMasks
cjnIcmpInAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

cjnIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: cjnIcmpInAddrMaskReps
cjnIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

cjnIcmpOutMsgs.name: cjnIcmpOutMsgs
cjnIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

cjnIcmpOutErrors.name: cjnIcmpOutErrors
cjnIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter'svalue.

cjnIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: cjnIcmpOutDestUnreachs
cjnIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: cjnIcmpOutTimeExcds
cjnIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutParmProbs.name: cjnIcmpOutParmProbs
cjnIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: cjnIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
cjnIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutRedirects.name: cjnIcmpOutRedirects
cjnIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

cjnIcmpOutEchos.name: cjnIcmpOutEchos
cjnIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutEchoReps.name: cjnIcmpOutEchoReps
cjnIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutTimestamps.name: cjnIcmpOutTimestamps
cjnIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: cjnIcmpOutTimestampReps
cjnIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: cjnIcmpOutAddrMasks
cjnIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

cjnIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: cjnIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
cjnIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

cjnUdpInDatagrams.name: cjnUdpInDatagrams
cjnUdpInDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams delivered to UDP users.

cjnUdpNoPorts.name: cjnUdpNoPorts
cjnUdpNoPorts.description: The total number of received UDP datagrams for which there was no application at the destination port.

cjnUdpInErrors.name: cjnUdpInErrors
cjnUdpInErrors.description: The number of received UDP datagrams that could not be delivered for reasons other than the lack of an application at the destination port.

cjnUdpOutDatagrams.name: cjnUdpOutDatagrams
cjnUdpOutDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams sent from this entity.

cjnIpNetToMediaTable.name: cjnIpNetToMediaTable
cjnIpNetToMediaTable.description: The IP Address Translation table used for mapping from IP addresses to physical addresses.

cjnIpNetToMediaEntry.name: cjnIpNetToMediaEntry
cjnIpNetToMediaEntry.description: Each entry contains one IpAddress to `physical' address equivalence.

cjnIpNetToMediaIfIndex.name: cjnIpNetToMediaIfIndex
cjnIpNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex. A value of 0 indicates that the entry is a static entry and does not bind to any interface.

cjnIpNetToMediaNetAddress.name: cjnIpNetToMediaNetAddress
cjnIpNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media- dependent `physical' address.

cjnIpNetToMediaRowStatus.name: cjnIpNetToMediaRowStatus
cjnIpNetToMediaRowStatus.description: The Status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active. notInService(2) -- Interface configured but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface NOT configured. createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnIpNetToMediaType.name: cjnIpNetToMediaType
cjnIpNetToMediaType.description: The type of mapping. The only vaild setting is to change from dynamic to static. Any other setting is invaild.
